
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `debcheckout` baraye gereftan (download) source code-e package-haye Debian az VCS (Version Control System), mesle Git ya Subversion, be kar mirevad.  In dastoor kar ra baraye modiriyate code va sakhte package-haye Debian asan mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `debcheckout package_name`  --> 📦 Gereftan source code-e package az VCS pishfarz.
    🔹 `debcheckout -d directory package_name`  --> 📂 Save kardane source code dar yek pooshe-ye moshakhas.
    🔹 `debcheckout -v`  --> 📢 Namayesh dadane etela'at bishtar dar morede process.
    🔹 `debcheckout -n`  --> ⛔️ Faghat neshan dadane dastoor-ha, vali anha ra ejra nakardan (dry run).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ debcheckout hello

    🔹 Gereftan source code-e package `hello` az VCS.

    $ debcheckout -d my_hello_source hello

    🔹 Gereftan source code-e package `hello` va zakhire kardane an dar pooshe-ye `my_hello_source`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ debcheckout -n hello

    🔹 Faghat dastoor-haii ke `debcheckout` baraye gereftan source code-e `hello` ejra mikonad ra namayesh midahad, vali hich amali ejra nemishavad.  In baraye check kardane chigonegi-ye kar kardane dastoor mohem ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `debcheckout` command is used to fetch (download) the source code of Debian packages from a Version Control System (VCS), such as Git or Subversion. It simplifies the process of code management and building Debian packages.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `debcheckout package_name`  --> 📦 Fetch the source code of the package from the default VCS.
    🔹 `debcheckout -d directory package_name`  --> 📂 Save the source code in a specified directory.
    🔹 `debcheckout -v`  --> 📢 Show more verbose information about the process.
    🔹 `debcheckout -n`  --> ⛔️ Only show the commands, but do not execute them (dry run).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ debcheckout hello

    🔹 Fetch the source code of the `hello` package from VCS.

    $ debcheckout -d my_hello_source hello

    🔹 Fetch the source code of the `hello` package and save it in the `my_hello_source` directory.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ debcheckout -n hello

    🔹 Shows the commands that `debcheckout` would execute to fetch the source code for `hello`, without actually executing them. This is useful for checking how the command works before running it.
